  "prompt": "Is there a way to see someones likes on instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, there are a few ways to see someone's liked posts:\n\n1. On their profile:\n- Go to their profile\n- Tap the three-line menu\n- Select \"Liked\"\n\n2. For private accounts:\n- You must be following them\n- Only works if they haven't disabled this feature\n\n3. Using third-party apps:\n- Some apps claim to show likes, but many violate Instagram's terms of service\n- These can be risky and might get your account suspended\n\n4. For your own account:\n- Go to \"Settings\" > \"Account\" > \"Posts You've Liked\"\n\nKeep in mind that Instagram has been changing its visibility settings, so these methods might not always work consistently.\n\nNote: Instagram has been moving towards hiding like counts and making likes more private, so the ability to see someone else's likes might be limited.",
